data.description: Do not miss your opportunity to own a home on 2 acres that has been cared for by the original owners! This home has so much to offer and is an incredible value! Come see for yourself the amount of care and consideration put into this property. The neighbors are excellent! Teller County currently has no short-term rental restrictions. Enjoy all year round or offer as a short-term rental when you are not living it! Endless possibilities!    This home sits on 2 acres and has been meticulously cared for by the original owners. The property boasts a remarkable 60'x40' heated and insulated shop that can accommodate up to seven vehicles. Equipped with two 14'x14' electric doors, you can pull through and conveniently drop trailers and maneuver your vehicles. Additionally, the shop features a covered 60'x14' area perfect for your RV or equipment storage needs. The large pull-through driveway also allows you to tow trailers with ease. The attached 2-car garage is heated, finished, and insulated. This home has a whole-house generator outlet that will allow you to power the home if you ever lose power. The road is plowed up to the beginning of the driveway, so you never have to worry about being snowed in.     The main level has a walk-in bathtub for easy accessibility. All bedrooms and laundry are on the main floor. The kitchen cabinets are upgraded and the drawers are soft-close and have dovetail joints.    The covered patio is 32'x26', with a floor-to-ceiling wood-burning fireplace and a swinging bed. Hot tub wiring and a concrete pad are pre-installed. Radiant heat is located in several areas of the home.    The seller-owned solar panels almost completely eliminate your electricity bill. Teller wifi is available for reliable internet.    Close proximity to Mueller State Park, 11 Mile Reservoir, and Florissant Fossil Bed National Monument. Enjoy hundreds of miles of hiking, biking, horseback riding, and off-road vehicle trails.
